sentences: While only in his teens, Bad Boy Bill began his DJ career in 1985 during the Chicago house music movement of the mid to late 1980s.
In 1988 and 1989, he was placed within the top three at the Disco Mix Club championships.
Between 1987 and 1995, Bill produced a series of promotional mixtapes under the name "Street DJ Promotions."

Bill created MCM in 1995 to produce legally licensed mixes, and as an umbrella company for several side projects and record labels such as International House Records (IHR), Moody Recordings, Contaminated Muzik, Canvas Recordings, and Motus Music.
They have released three mix albums, the last in 2013.
In May 2006, Bill reunited with Vission in Dallas and Detroit for a two-day reunion show.
In 2003, Bill released a CD/DVD mixtape titled Behind the Decks.
In May 2006, to support the Behind the Decks mixtape, Bill embarked on a three-day tour called "BTD Live".
Audio and video were recorded at all three shows and released as the BTD Live concert film in October 2006.
On August 5, 2013, The Official Bad Boy Bill YouTube page released House Connection 3, a free mixtape available to download on Richard Vission's SoundCloud page.

While only in his teens, Bad Boy Bill began his DJ career in 1985 during the Chicago house music movement of the mid to late 1980s.
Currently, Bad Boy Bill plays music ranging from House to Electro, and is known for playing six separate turntables at once.
Bad Boy Bill also made an uncredited appearance as the club DJ in the opening scene of the 1998 film Blade.
1999 URB Magazine Readers Poll 2nd Place DJ of the Year
1998 Winter Music Conference Mixshow DJ of the Year
